&nbsp;Mary and Michael are supposed to be splitting up they&#8217;ve both found someone else but then they find themselves unexpectedly rekindling their marriage.Can they get back together before it&#8217;s too late?May 2017 comedy &#8220;The Lovers&#8221; stars Debra Winger of &#8220;In Treatment&#8221; and &#8220;The Ranch&#8221; as Mary and Tracy Letts of &#8220;Homeland&#8221; and &#8220;The Big Short&#8221; ans Michael.Opposite them and, it would seem, opposing their plans to stay married are Aiden Gillen (&#8220;Game of Thrones&#8221;) and Melora Walters (&#8220;Magnolia.&#8221;)Winger picked up three Academy Award nominations for &#8220;Shadowlands,&#8221; &#8220;Terms of Endearment&#8221; and &#8220;An Officer and a Gentleman&#8221; while Letts received consecutive annual Screen Actors Guild Award nominations for &#8220;Homeland&#8221; and a Writers Guild nmoination for &#8220;August: Osage County,&#8221; which he wrote both as a play and then for cinema.Writer-director Azazel Jacobs was behind 2011&#8217;s &#8220;Terri,&#8221; nominated for the Grand Jury Prize at Sundance.-Relaxnews